reviews.text: Five stars for customer service. I had a medical issue and management couldn't do enough to help and followed up re my recovery.  Easy walk to trains, buses. Short walk to promenade. Comfortable clean rooms. Highly recommend this property.

Overall, the stay is okay but the front desk service needs improvement. 

The Good - Though old, the room is nice and comfortable. Coupled with a good location and a nice breakfast spread.

The Bad - The gym is sparse but makes up for it by opening 24 hours. 

The Ugly - Front counter staff was nonchalant and non-welcoming for guests. Arrived on time but rooms are unavailable and offer no solution other than asking us to come back later. When back later, the rooms are still unavailable. The waiting time for lifts/elevators are also equally horrid, even though the hotel has only 3 levels of basement, ground floor and 14 floors above.

I can't find enough words of praise for this excellent hotel. It is situated in a very convenient position in Kowloon. The rooms are very clean and up to date. Breakfast every morning was terrific. The staff were very helpful and friendly. A big thank you to especially the front office manager Maureen Hung.  I had lost my phone in a taxi and someone found it but couldn't return it to the hotel. Maureen went out of her way to get it delivered back to the hotel. Thank you Maureen for your professionalism. Also I would like to thank Warren for answering all my silly questions and being so helpful at the front desk too with regards to my lost phone. I really recommend this great motel to everyone.
Totally recommend staying at the Regal Kowloon.

A really great experience. Exhausted each day after our sightseeing it was such a joy to return to the peace and quiet of this lovely hotel.  We upgraded from our standard  booking to Executive in order to benefit from a range of extras including use of the Executive  Suite where we enjoyed all the treats. Well worth the extra if you travelling. Late Check-Out , Free Airport Shuttle, Superior rooms, Free drinks Etc, Etc, The staff in the Executive Suite were all very pleasant and helpful . All in all a very pleasant stay. Highly recommended.

Conveniently located, 5 minutes away from TST subway station. Had no view in my room and the room was very humid. Considerably spacious when compared to other 3-4 star hotels and the interior design seem to be out dated. There are certainly better options available within the same area but you get what you paid for. The staff are nice and very helpful. Again, it all comes down to budgeting, you get what you paid for.
